Sheridan hits out at egg thugsPOLITICIAN Tommy Sheridan hit out at thugs who egged his Glasgow home.The ex-Socialist MSP his young daughter Gabrielle has been left terrified by the incident on Monday night.Mr Sheridan tweeted: &quot;Just had house windows egged by four thugs.&quot;Wee Gabrielle is very upset.&quot;He reported to the incident to police.A Police Scotland spokeswoman said: &quot;Police called around 8.25pm on Monday June 22 to a report of eggs thrown at a house in Cardonald, Glasgow.&quot;Police advice was given.&quot;Mr Sheridan had tweeted that sectarian abuse had also been shouted as the eggs where thrown.However, police said there was no report of sectarian abuse.